summary: Her daydreams about lovely things - silks, jewels, lemon cakes – are reserved for only the most desperate of times, when she...
text: Her daydreams about lovely things - silks, jewels, lemon cakes – are reserved for only the most desperate of times, when she must disappear inside herself to forget the pain and sorrow of the world, like yesterday in front of the heart tree, where her mind had been whisked away to some imagined land of finery where she lay on a couch soothed by a river-side breeze, eating sweets from a golden platter.

description: The hall, or what passed for a hall North of the Wall, bustled with laughter and stories, heated by a roaring hearth, warm bodies, and hot food. The old wildling mothers had performed a minor miracle and cobbled together a halfway respectable feast with the paltry kitchen they were working with. Either way, the spiced pigeon and venison provided for a richer meal than the regimented meals that the camp normally ate. They had managed to scrounge up enough eating utensils for everyone but the Free Folk insisted on using their hands, “As the Old Gods intended.”
